  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Mix the ricotta cheese with the lemon juice, garlic, salt, and black pepper in a bowl.",
    "Mix the goose fat with the chopped parsley, dill, mint, salt, and black pepper in a separate bowl.",
    "Lay a ssam-wrap on a flat surface and brush with olive oil.",
    "Spread the ricotta mixture on the center of the wrap, leaving a 1-inch border around the edges.",
    "Fold the bottom edge of the wrap up over the filling, then fold in the sides and roll the wrap into a neat cylindrical shape.",
    "Place the wrapped roll seam-side down on a baking sheet and brush with the goose fat mixture.",
    "Bake the wrap for 15 minutes, or until crispy and golden brown.",
    "While the wrap is baking, toast the chopped walnuts in a dry pan over medium heat until fragrant and lightly browned.",
    "Sprinkle the toasted walnuts, crumbled feta cheese, chopped kalamata olives, and sesame seeds over the wrap.",
    "Drizzle with additional lemon juice and sprinkle with chopped fresh lavender and red pepper flakes.",
    "Cut in half to serve.",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with additional parsley and lemon zest if desired."
  ],
